The paper focuses on natural language understanding and reasoning, which are core topics in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of pre-trained models and transfer learning also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The regularization techniques and feature engineering may also fall under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
